<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">PortlyBugger</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok I realize that after every patch people used to get on Whineplay and complain that sow is slower/clarity is slower/resists are higher/etc. but bear me out.<P>I went to Chardok and Karnor's tonight and pullers in both groups were complaining of mobs jumping them from MUCH longer distances than before.  These are guys who have pulled these places a lot (chardok puller is a 59 war, karnor's puller is a 57 ranger) and are familiar with how it usually works.  <P>Add to that random trains at places like Charok entrance, where I'm used to seeing 2 things tops (we were the only ones in the zone) and it makes me think something's different.  Just wondering if anybody saw anything similar.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">preiter</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Now that you mention it...<P>I was pulling in the Karnor sewers last night with my level 56 monk. I took 2 steps into the Verix Kylox's remains room and the whole room aggroed all at once.<P>I feigned immediately, and the whole mess poured out of the room onto my group in the next room.<P>Later, we were in the tunnel that comes from the moat, going back in. We were fighting a sentry when suddenly there were 6 or so mobs on us out of nowhere. The sewers is not a usual place to be trained.<P>Mostly things seemed normal, but these 2 incidents were definitely weird.<P>------------------<BR><B>Merpa Gigglesnort, Muerta Bella, Shakah Lakalaka</B><BR>Citizen of the Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mirriana_00</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Were the remains up?  It has a horribly large aggro radius.  I once inched up to the door to take a look, and almost before I could see it I got the whole room on me.<P>Works kind of like the Avatar of Fear in Cazic.  If you can see it, it's too late.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Astur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wow, similar experience in the Verix area last night. We were pulling all along, no problems. Then we pulled from outside, got like 5 and thought, no biggie, AOE time! Well, about 10 more things came! Needless to say we had a bunch of dead level 59s and 60s. =)<BR><P>------------------<BR>Astur il'Ayan, Cleric of Brell<BR>Dealers of Death on Solusek Ro<BR>Profile  <A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=50334" TARGET=_blank>http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=50334</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pacemaker</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The plane of Hate and plane of Fear didn't seem to have a bigger aggro range.<P>The only thing changed in PoF, is that they gave Cazic Thule a higher MR so he is practically impossible to slow : 3 of our shamans (lvl.60) ran out of mana trying.<P>He went down anyways and Halo dropped so not bad after all...  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR>Pacemaker <BR>57 Templar <BR>Spirit of Tunare - The Rathe</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jassie</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">just back from CT raid, i would guess the slowable version of CT is gone. (was the CHer in taunt group, somehow DP saved me in the 5min fight  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/biggrin.gif">  )</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wendel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">yep, and I got the Halo WOOOOOOOT!  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
